Combine garlic, pepper, fish sauce, sugar, orange juice, vinegar, and chile paste in small saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer 3 minutes until mixture thickens slightly. Let cool. Place shrimp in large bowl. Add 3 tablespoons of marinade, tossing well to coat shrimp and rubbing into flesh. Chill 30 minutes. Reserve remaining marinade. Coat grill rack with cooking spray and preheat grill to medium-high. Skewer shrimp and grill 3 to 4 minutes or until just cooked through, turning once and brushing with reserved marinade.